Do you know how much equity you have in your home?

If you're a homeowner, your net worth has gotten a big boost recently! That's because home appreciation over the last handful of years has increased your equity. Here's what you need to know!

What is equity?
Equity is the current value of your home minus what you owe on the loan. It increases when:
-You pay down your loan over time
-Home price appreciation drives up your home's value
Since this time last year, the average home owner's equity grew by $55,300!

How it benefits you?
You can use rising home equity to fuel a move. It may be some (if not all) of what you need for a down payment on your next home!

Ready to sell? Reach out to us and let's talk about how you can use that equity to fuel your next move.

For the last 20 years I have been one of Nashville’s Top Men’s Hairstylists, and for the last 4 years I have been a Realtor. Doing both brings me so much joy. 

My love for doing hair will always be, but this new found love for real estate has been so exciting. 
It’s all about my amazing clients. I have always loved meeting new people and creating lasting relationships. 

I am a Luxury Agent and my team is one of the best in the business, but I work with all price points and properties. For me it’s about client care over commission.

I tell my clients all the time, “Get out of your dreams, and get in to your home!” 

If you’re looking to buy or sell, or just have questions about the Nashville market. I hope you’ll reach out and give me the opportunity to make your real estate dreams a reality.

💰 Is Nashville The Most Expensive City in the South?
Hardly!

According to the most recent data, Nashville’s cost of living index is 95.4, slightly below the National Average (source: @nashchamber) and less than similar metros like Austin, Atlanta, Seattle, and Chicago. This means more bang for your buck without sacrificing the vibrant lifestyle you seek! 🌆💵

And let’s talk taxes: Nashville’s tax burden is also much lower than average, at $4,041. Compare that to $6,806 in Charlotte or $9,208 in Louisville! What’s the difference? Tennessee has ZERO state income tax.

More savings in your pocket means more opportunities to enjoy the fantastic music, food, and culture that our city has to offer. 🎶🍴

🏛️ CELEBRATE Nashville's Public Works: The Library 📚
This is the first in a series celebrating architectural wonders of Nashville, starting with the magnificent Nashville Public Library — a shining example of responsible city investment! 🌆

📖 The Main Library: Nashville takes pride in its world-class library system, boasting the stunning Main Library and five branches. Did you know that in June 2001, the new 300,000 sq. ft. Main Library opened its doors at 615 Church St.? It's a testament to the city's commitment to education and culture, with a design by Robert A.M. Stern Architects.

📆 Historical Milestones:
• June 24, 1997: Metro Council approves the building of the new Main Library and five branches, at a cost of $98 million.
• 2010: Nashville Public Library receives the National Medal for Museum and Library Science.
• 2017: Nashville Public Library is honored as Library of the Year by Library Journal and Gale.

📣 I loved this quote from Betsy Fisher, Retired Former Library Manager:
" ...At the last moment the Circulation Manager pointed out that the Circulation Workroom was on the east side and it meant all the carts of books to be shelved would have to go through the lobby or down a floor... We all agreed that didn’t make sense. The architect said 'not a problem,' took his pencil and flipped the sides! And that is how the Teen Area ended up with such a primo view of the garden."

Nashville's public buildings stand as testaments to our city's commitment to education, culture, and community. So proud to call this community my home!

Nic, 

Happy 30th Birthday! 
We all miss you. 

I’m so angry and mad and pissed that you’re not here. 
I want answers. 
Answers I’ll never get. 

This sucks. 

I have questions and I want answers. 
I’ll never know those answers until I see you again. 

What I do know is that you gave the BEST hugs.
You were selfless. 
You gave your all to the people you loved and you loved hard. 

You did so much in your short time here. 
More than most people do their whole lives. 

You put time in perspective. 
 
I have come to the realization that I can’t question God. 
Only HE knows. 

I have comfort knowing you were saved and baptized not long before you left.

Grief, I’ve learned, is really just love. 

It’s all the love you want to give, but cannot. 

All that unspent love gathers up in the corners of your eyes, the lump in your throat, and in that hollow part of your chest. 

Grief is just love with no place to go. 

Until we see  you again!

Happy 30th, Nicolas Henry Kerdiles! 

Gone but NEVER forgotten ❤️‍🩹
